Crystal Lake Metabolism

DO%sat and DO mass:

Figure 1: Crystal Lake volume weighted dissolved oxygen percent saturation (A) and total dissolved oxygen mass (B). NOTES (1) This is nothing new. I provided it for context.

NEP:

Figure 2: Depth integrated NEP (grey points) and moving average (red line). NEP = delta.O2 - flux.O2, where delta.O2 is the change in the areal whole lake dissolved oxygen between consecutive 6 hour profiles, and flux.O2 is the O2 flux between the atmosphere and lake calculated every minute and integrated over the 6 hour period between profiles. The k.gas model used for calculation is Cole and Caraco 1998. NOTES: (1) This could be a good way to visualize NEP if the moving average could be improved. I used linear interpolation (nearest neighbor) to fill missing data, but perhaps filling missing data with average values a day or two on either end of the gap would be better.

Figure 3: Depth integrated NEP averaged to periods before, during, and after stratification. NOTES: (1) Average daily NEP observed throughout the stratification period of 2012 and 2013 roughly accords with the observed -10 mmol/m^2/d decrease in whole lake dissolved oxygen during these periods. (2) Positive NEP observed after 2012 stratification may be a result of sparse data coverage that is biasing periods of production. Ill look into this further.

Figure 4: Upper Mixed Layer NEP vs.Depth Integrated NEP. Dashed line is 1:1. NEP is calculated every 6 hours. NEP for the entire open water period of each year is included in this figure. NOTES: (1) This is the plot Steve wanted to see.

Figure 5: Upper Mixed Layer NEP vs.Depth Integrated NEP. Dashed line is 1:1. Solid line is the type II major axis regression. Regression equation and correlation coefficient are presented. NEP is calculated every 6 hours. NEP for the entire open water period is included in this figure. NOTES: (1) This is just a quick and dirty regression to give some sense of the trends you can probably see with your eyes. (2) NEP.UML is underestimated with respect to NEP.DI when Crystal is unmixed. This accords with the metalimnetic/hypolimnetic chlorophyll maximum observed during unmixed years. Similarly, when Crystal is mixed, the chlorophyll maximum moved into the epilimnion and NEP.UML became over estimated with respect to NEP.DI.
